                            <comment id="13247100" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 5 Apr 2012 09:03:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4098&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4098&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13254324" author="njiang" created="Sun, 15 Apr 2012 13:25:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;HttpClient will close the InputStream automatically, when the connection is closed.&lt;br/&gt;
So we need to cache the InputStream in the HttpProducer before close the connection.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13262297" author="njiang" created="Thu, 26 Apr 2012 00:58:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Christian&lt;br/&gt;
Please check out my comment in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4098&quot; title=&quot;camel-http - Apparently it forces the streamcache&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-4098&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-4098&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. We still need to cache the input stream by default.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13262669" author="chris@die-schneider.net" created="Thu, 26 Apr 2012 15:28:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removing the Caching and the releasing of the connection. If the inputstream is closed later the connection should be released. If it does not happen then a waorkaround would be a manual convertBodyTo as the converter closes the stream&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13396512" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 19 Jun 2012 04:59:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4098&quot; title=&quot;camel-http - Apparently it forces the streamcache&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-4098&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-4098&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
